---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import ReviewCard from '../components/ReviewCard.astro';
---

<Base title="Stay Nivas — Where You Dwell Matters">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        <span class="hero-stay">Stay</span> <span class="hero-nivas">Nivas</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">Where you dwell matters.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder's Note -->
  <section class="founders-note">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="note-content">
        <p>
          I stopped trusting hotel reviews the day I realized they were all answering the wrong question. Thread count, pool temperature, breakfast buffet variety. Useful, sure. But not why I remember the places I remember.
        </p>
        <p>
          The hotels that stayed with me did something else. They changed the rhythm of my day. They made me notice things I normally walk past. They understood something about rest that goes deeper than a good mattress.
        </p>
        <p>
          Stay Nivas is my attempt to write about that. Not what a hotel has, but what it does to you. The reviews here are personal, sometimes imperfect, and always honest. If a place earned my attention, I'll tell you why. If it didn't, I'll tell you that too.
        </p>
        <p class="note-sign">
          Yash Kothari<br />
          <span class="note-title">Founder, Stay Nivas</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reviews -->
  <section class="reviews" id="reviews">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Reviews</h2>

      <ReviewCard
        title="Hyatt Regency The Churchill"
        subtitle="The small touches that make a big hotel feel personal"
        location="London, England"
        date="February 2026"
        rating={5}
        summary="The Churchill doesn't dazzle. It does something harder: it makes a family with a toddler feel completely at ease in Mayfair. Juan and Guillaume set the tone before we arrived, and every interaction after that confirmed it. The Regency Suite was generous, housekeeping was impeccable, and the service throughout was the kind that treats families as the point, not a tolerated exception."
        image="/images/hyatt-churchill/hero.jpg"
        imageAlt="London skyline at dusk, Mayfair"
        slug="hyatt-regency-the-churchill-london"
      />

      <ReviewCard
        title="Andaz Peninsula Papagayo"
        subtitle="Where the jungle decides what kind of guest you'll be"
        location="Guanacaste, Costa Rica"
        date="November 2024"
        rating={5}
        summary="Five nights for a babymoon that set a new standard. The Andaz doesn't announce itself; it lets the Pacific and the dry tropical forest do that. What set it apart was the wellness program, genuinely woven into the property's identity, and a team led by Henrique, Paola, and Manolo who made hospitality feel personal rather than transactional. Even surpassed the nearby Four Seasons."
        image="/images/andaz-papagayo/hero.jpg"
        imageAlt="View of Culebra Bay from the Andaz Papagayo through tropical foliage"
        slug="andaz-peninsula-papagayo"
      />

      <ReviewCard
        title="Soho House Mumbai"
        subtitle="The rooftop where Mumbai finally sits still"
        location="Mumbai, India"
        date="January 2024"
        rating={5}
        summary="A babymoon in Juhu where the members' club DNA shaped everything for the better. The rooftop views of the city and the Arabian Sea set the backdrop, Cecconi's delivered genuinely excellent vegetarian Italian, and the room service was prompt and warm. Soho House understood the difference between vacation and 'we need a few days to just be' without us having to explain it."
        image="/images/soho-house-mumbai/hero.jpg"
        imageAlt="Mumbai skyline at dusk from Juhu"
        slug="soho-house-mumbai"
      />

      <ReviewCard
        title="The Beekman"
        subtitle="A lobby that remembers New York"
        location="New York, USA"
        date="2023"
        rating={5}
        summary="A staycation that cleared the high bar of being worthwhile for New Yorkers. The nine-story Victorian atrium is stunning, but it's the consistency of taste throughout, from the rooms to the restaurants to the elevators, that makes The Beekman more than a pretty lobby. Lauren, Justin, and Alex set the service tone before we even arrived."
        image="/images/the-beekman/hero.jpg"
        imageAlt="The Beekman Hotel's Victorian atrium"
        slug="the-beekman-new-york"
      />

      <ReviewCard
        title="Ca' di Dio"
        subtitle="One night that felt like a full stay"
        location="Venice, Italy"
        date="2023"
        rating={5}
        summary="Proof that one night is enough to know a hotel is exceptional. A restored 15th-century hospice with Patricia Urquiola interiors that honor Venice without imitating it. Christophe, Filippo, and Matteo made us feel like week-long guests in a single evening. In a city where hotels often coast on location, Ca' di Dio has its own point of view."
        image="/images/ca-di-dio/hero.jpg"
        imageAlt="Venice waterfront at golden hour"
        slug="ca-di-dio-venice"
      />

      <ReviewCard
        title="Sujan Rajmahal Palace"
        subtitle="Where heritage is a living thing, not a museum exhibit"
        location="Jaipur, India"
        date="2022"
        rating={5}
        summary="We came for a private dinner and left knowing we'd return for a full stay. Rajmahal Palace carries the weight of a maharaja's residence but the Sujan team has made it feel alive rather than preserved. The vegetarian courses were exceptional, and the hospitality from Arun and Yashpal embodied mehman-nawazi: the genuine Indian pleasure in hosting."
        image="/images/sujan-rajmahal/hero.jpg"
        imageAlt="Sujan Rajmahal Palace exterior at dusk"
        slug="sujan-rajmahal-jaipur"
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 6rem 0 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.25em;
  }

  .hero-stay { font-weight: 400; }
  .hero-nivas { font-weight: 700; }

  .hero-tagline {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem);
    color: var(--color-slate);
  }

  .founders-note {
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-warm-sand);
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .note-content {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-saffron);
  }

  .note-content p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
  }

  .note-sign {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .note-title {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .reviews { padding: 0 0 4rem; }

  .section-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-warm-sand);
  }
</style>
